  "guidance": [
    {
      "type": "Change From Last Year",
      "text": "Modified question (2025 7.12.1)",
      "typeKo": "전년 대비 변경사항",
      "textKo": "전년 대비 변경사항은 2026 CDP 원문 및 변경 추적표 기준으로 확인하십시오."
    },
    {
      "type": "Question Dependencies",
      "text": "This question appears if you select \"Yes, in our direct operations\" or \"Yes, in both our direct operations and our upstream/downstream value chain\" in response to 7.12 column \"Agriculture, forestry or other land sector activities\".",
      "typeKo": "문항 의존성",
      "textKo": "이 섹션은 문항 응답에 필요한 추가 작성 기준을 설명합니다. 응답방법과 선택지를 함께 확인하여 작성하십시오."
    },
    {
      "type": "Requested Content",
      "text": "General \nThe GHG Protocol has developed a new Land Sector and Removals Standard (LSRS) and Guidance . Due to the timeline of publication, organizations are not yet able to report emissions and removals in line with the LSRS in CDP's 2026 corporate questionnaire. However, this question allows you to report CO2 emissions from biogenic carbon in alignment with the GHG Protocol Corporate Standard .\nThis question remains in the 2026 CDP questionnaire to maintain alignment with the GHG Protocol Corporate Standard until the questionnaire is updated to enable companies to report land-related emissions in line with the LSRS. If biogenic carbon is relevant to your organization but not yet calculated, leave this question blank rather than reporting 0.\nCO2 emissions from biogenic carbon (metric tons CO2) (column 1) \nPlease enter your total direct emissions of CO2 from biogenic carbon, for example, CO2 emissions from combustion of biofuels.\nThis figure specifically requests information on direct CO2 emissions that occur from sources that are owned or controlled by the company. However, if you would like to report your indirect emissions from biogenic carbon, you can report this in the Comment column, outlining the quantity and source(s) of these emissions. \nDo not include other GHGs emitted from the combustion of biomass or fermentation (e.g. nitrous oxide and methane are emitted from the combustion of biomass/biofuel). These should be reported within Scope 1, 2 or 3 (whichever is relevant to your company).",
      "typeKo": "요청 내용",
      "textKo": "이 섹션은 해당 문항에서 CDP가 요청하는 작성 내용을 설명합니다. 응답방법, 열 구조, 드롭다운 선택지를 기준으로 보고연도와 조직 범위에 맞는 정보를 입력하십시오."
    },
    {
      "type": "Additional Information",
      "text": "Biogenic materials, including biomass, biofuels, and biogas, are increasingly used as a resource for energy generation. While biomass can produce fewer GHG emissions than fossil fuels and may be grown and used on a shorter time horizon, it still produces GHG emissions and should not be treated with a \"zero\" emission factor.\nBased on the GHG Protocol Corporate Accounting and Reporting Standard , any emissions of CH4 or N2O from biologically sequestered carbon shall be reported in scope 1, 2 or 3, while the emissions of CO2 shall be reported outside the scopes. In practice, for scope 2 emissions this means that any market-based method data that includes biofuels should report the CO2 portion of the biofuel combustion separately from the scope. Please refer to GHG Protocol Scope 2 Guidance for more details.",
      "typeKo": "추가 정보",
      "textKo": "이 섹션은 응답 작성 시 참고할 수 있는 추가 설명입니다. 필요한 경우 관련 기준, 방법론, 내부 검토 자료를 근거로 활용하십시오."
    }
  ],
